race.comment: Really think PARTY CRASHER (3) can improve sharply on his first-up run and win this. He is a progressive 4-year-old that would've gone close in the Queensland Derby if he hadn't been a late scratching. The step to 1800m looks ideal here and Todd Pannell should give him every opportunity from barrier four. PELEVECCHIO (12) has placed both runs this campaign. She has the ability to win this, but she's becoming a frustrating proposition for punters. Expect her to loom as a winning threat but whether she can go on with the job is a different story. FLAMING NAVY (8) won an easier race at Balaklava last start but he did it in the manner of a horse destined for greater heights. He will roll forward and take some beating. LONGER ROUTE (2) is a likely improver, while SUPER LAD (5) is in career-best form and must be included on the quick back-up.
